<summary>
The <strong><c>color</c></strong> CSS property sets the foreground <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/color_value">color value</see> of an element&amp;apos;s text and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/text-decoration">text decorations</see>, and sets the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/color_value#currentcolor_keyword"><c>currentcolor</c></see> value. <c>currentcolor</c> may be used as an indirect value on <strong>other</strong> properties and is the default for other color properties, such as <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/border-color">border-color</see>.
</summary>
